      "text": "Here's where behavioural activation comes in again, this time on the upswing. Rising energy is an opportunity, and the best thing you can do with it is spend it on things you value. Not because you must exercise or be productive, but because using your returning energy on activities that matter to you does two powerful things: it makes you feel even better (movement and engagement lift mood and further build energy), and it ties your freedom to a richer life rather than to mere absence of smoking.\n\nThis matters for staying free. \"Not smoking\" is a void; a void is hard to defend forever. But \"I'm someone who walks, who has the energy for my kids, who took up something I'd been too sluggish for\" — that's a positive identity that has no room for a cigarette in it. You don't protect freedom by guarding an empty space. You protect it by filling your life with things the old you was too drained to do."
